replies.bodyText:
The motivation to put it only in the ServerErrorException class was that the standard error message of a ClientErrorException is already a client-facing one, i.e. it is used in the HTTP response for example:



      hono/adapters/http-vertx-base/src/main/java/org/eclipse/hono/adapter/http/AbstractVertxBasedHttpProtocolAdapter.java


        Lines 787 to 789
      in
      0e440ef







           if (ClientErrorException.class.isInstance(t)) { 




               outcome = ProcessingOutcome.UNPROCESSABLE; 




               ctx.fail(t); 





I see a ServerErrorException as more of an internal exception, where it makes sense to add a separate error message that abstracts from the internals.

